  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Passport for Education &#x2013; Phase Three</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will be implemented in support of the Federal Government, in the context of Brazil&apos;s broader voluntary relocation programme of Venezuelans from the border states of Roraima and Amazonas to other Brazilian states. In particular, the project aims to support the voluntary relocation process and integration of Venezuelan refugees and migrants by providing families with children and adolescents with adequate information and about education rights in Brazil. This includes promoting widespread understanding about the Brazilian education system and how to transfer and enroll their children in school upon relocation. The project also aims to identify and document good practices and policies related to school transfer and integration of relocated Venezuelan children and adolescents in major cities of destination. The overall objective of the project is, thus, to contribute to an increased access to education of relocated Venezuelan refugee and migrant children and adolescents, in line with priority needs, as in the 2021 Refugee and Migrant Response Plan.</narrative>
  </description>
